{
  "texts": [
    "Non-repudiationIn the IoT, non-repudiation is necessary, ensuring that services serving as a link between the smooth transmission of service/data and effective security implementation can be allowed or disowned [120,121].",
    "ConfidentialityConfidentiality within IoT security involves safeguarding sensitive information and data from unauthorized access, disclosure, or exposure.",
    "It constitutes a vital necessity, and this safeguarding can be guaranteed by implementing secure encryption methods [122,123].",
    "The difference between confidentiality and integrity is that Confidentiality relies on password-based encryption for protection.",
    "In contrast, integrity, specifically against memory tampering, is maintained using a message authentication code derived from the stored context [124]."
  ]
}